      "name": "Multiattack",
      "type": "creatureFeature",
      "img": "icons/svg/sword.svg",
      "system": {
        "key": "creatureMultiattack",
        "description": "<p><strong>What it does (SRD):</strong> When the creature makes a <strong>full attack</strong> that includes its <strong>primary</strong> natural weapon, its <strong>secondary</strong> natural weapons are rolled with a reduced attack penalty compared to the usual full-attack stacking. The Monster Manual phrasing is typically <strong>secondary attacks at −5</strong> from the creature’s best natural attack bonus, or <strong>only −2</strong> behind the primary when the primary natural weapon is a <strong>bite</strong>.</p><p><strong>ThirdEra:</strong> This item leaves <strong>Mechanical effects</strong> empty on its <strong>Details</strong> tab. Natural attack bonuses come from the NPC sheet’s <strong>Natural attacks</strong> list: mark each attack as primary or secondary; the sheet uses full melee for primaries and <strong>full melee − 5</strong> for secondaries unless you enter a <strong>preset attack bonus</strong> on a row so it matches the printed stat block (for example, true dragons where secondaries are only −2 behind the bite).</p>",
